“LA Closet Design is trulv a one-stop shop for your closet transformation. From inventory to installation, we execute each stage of the design and build process to ensure a final result that is nothing less than perfection.” 💖💖💖

Treat your closet like an extension of your living spaces — decorate with drapery, furniture, accessories, and lighting! 💕✨

IKYMI in print - we were featured in @paradisevalleycitylifestyle to talk celebrity closets, and share some tips for seasonal wardrobe swapping! Link to the full article in stories 🫶🏼
1. ���Purge regularly. Make sure the items you bring into your dream dressing room are truly the pieces you love and will wear. If something doesn’t fit or isn’t being worn, take action. Tailor it, donate it, or consign it!
2. ���Invest in the right hangers. This is an easy way to instantly elevate the look of your closet, and using proper hangers for sweaters, suits, and outerwear will extend the life of your clothes.
3. ���Customize your drawers. Outfitting drawers with appropriate compartments makes life so much easier. Partitioning deeper drawers for folded tees, sweaters, and sweats means never having to dig.
4. ���Have a system. I like to organize clients’ clothing by style and color, so finding the piece you’re looking for is always easy. Whatever your system is, stick to it.
5. ���Protect your investments. Often, accessories are the most valuable pieces in our closets, and they end up overlooked. Care for your designer bags with properly-sized purse pillows, and appropriate shelf heights, so nothing gets crushed or creased. Incorporate safes, watch winders, and suede jewelry inserts so all your valuables are taken care of.
